ELYTRA. Fine striae, dark blue-green, with superficially impressed punctures, scabriculous, impressed basally as distinct fossae. Interstriae black, scabriculous, partially roughened, with superficially impressed punctures. Sutural margin without apical tooth (
Fig. 13A
).

GENITALIA. Right lobe of endophallite copulatrix more developed than left lobe. Right lobe obtusely triangular in shape, sharply acute frontally, rounded superiorly. Left lobe strongly developed, obtusely lobed. Central ridge more developed than central column (
Fig. 1O
).
